column10:
TL;DR A pixel roguelike sandbox beat’em up second to none

Wot I liked
- Cool pixel artstyle: many models, skins, weapons, guns, items and animations really liven the game up;
- Tongue in cheek sarcastic writing;
- Classes, traits, items, perks, custom classes;
- Melee combat is not as simple as it looks — you can kinda block and time your attacks;
- The goal of the game is to depose the mayor: you can do it by force or through elections;
- Classes - you can play as a bruiser, killing everyone. Or be a stealth assassin. Or be a bartender and serve everyone drinks. Or be a vampire and drink everyone’s blood. Or be a zombie and start a zombie apocalypse;
- The game has 5 districts (Slums, Industrial, Park, Downtown, Uptown) with 3 sub areas + Mayor’s Village. Each area consists of a small part of town with its own factions, locales, facilities for you to wreak havoc.

Wot I disliked
- As it's a roguelike each run is a bit too long - my first successful run took about 2 hours;
- Unlocking all the traits takes quite some time;
- Highlight all command does not highlight interactive items;
- The number of traits/rewards you can remove in order to customize your run is not big enough.

To sum it all up, Streets of Rogue is an excellent pixel roguelike sandbox RPG.

If you're reading this review wondering if you should get it, [i]you should get it.[/i]
This is easily one of the most fun games I've ever played.

Look, the best part about the game is the freedom; you can approach a given mission in the randomly generated worlds in any way you want. You gotta free a guy from prison? You could: 
walk in and kill the guard up to get the key, sure you could be boring;
or you could sneak in behind the guard and pick the lock on the door; 
or you could hack the computer from outside to open the door; 
or you could just break through the wall with certain traits; 
or you could buy a slave with an explosive collar, tell him to go stand near the wall, and blow him up;
or you could tell your newfound gorilla friend whom you hired with a banana to beat the crap out of the guard

point is the game allows you to be creative.
